summary: This is an email chain from July 2020 among US Attorney's Office (SDNY) and FBI personnel, discussing scheduling for the following week. It mentions a need to fix a typo in the Ghislaine Maxwell indictment before a grand jury and references two remaining statutory victims as a priority.

persons.name: Mimi
persons.context: Appears as an FBI recipient copied on an email regarding scheduling for the Maxwell case.

events.title: Grand jury session to fix Maxwell indictment typo
events.description: A prosecutor needs to appear before the grand jury to correct a typographical error in the indictment against Ghislaine Maxwell.

keyFacts: The document is an internal email chain from July 2020 regarding case scheduling among SDNY and FBI personnel.
It reveals a procedural detail: a prosecutor needed to go before a grand jury to fix a typo in the Ghislaine Maxwell indictment.
The email mentions 'two of the remaining statutory victims' as a priority for the schedule, indicating ongoing victim coordination.
All sender/recipient names except 'Mimi' (FBI) are redacted, shown as placeholders like (USANYS) and (NY).
